� Key Takeaways 
1. ✅ @RestController - For building REST APIs 
2. ✅ ResponseEntity - Control HTTP status codes 
3. ✅ @Service - Business logic layer 
4. ✅ @RequestBody - Convert JSON to Java object 
5. ✅ @PathVariable - Extract ID from URL 
6. ✅ HTTP Methods - POST, GET, PUT, DELETE for CRUD 
7. ✅ Status Codes - 200, 201, 204, 404, 409 
8. ✅ Postman - Test REST APIs 
9. ✅ In-Memory Storage - ArrayList for learning 
10. ✅ Layered Architecture - Controller → Service → Storage 
